"What is the skeletal system?","The framework of bones supporting the body"
"What are the functions of the skeleton?","Support protection movement blood cell production"
"What is a long bone?","A bone longer than it is wide e.g. femur"
"What is a short bone?","A small cube-shaped bone e.g. carpals"
"What is a flat bone?","A thin bone e.g. ribs"
"What is an irregular bone?","A bone with complex shape e.g. vertebrae"
"What is the axial skeleton?","Central bones including skull and spine"
"What is the appendicular skeleton?","Limbs and girdles"
"What is a joint?","Where two bones meet"
"What is a hinge joint?","Allows flexion and extension e.g. elbow"
"What is a ball and socket joint?","Allows movement in all directions e.g. hip"
"What is a pivot joint?","Allows rotation e.g. neck"
"What is flexion?","Decreasing the angle at a joint"
"What is extension?","Increasing the angle at a joint"
"What is abduction?","Movement away from the midline"
"What is adduction?","Movement towards the midline"
"What is rotation?","Circular movement around an axis"
"What is circumduction?","Combination of movements forming a circle"
"What is the muscular system?","System of muscles enabling movement"
"What are antagonistic muscles?","Muscles working in pairs"
"What is an agonist?","Muscle causing movement"
"What is an antagonist?","Muscle opposing movement"
"What is a fixator?","Stabilises a joint"
"What is a synergist?","Assists the agonist"
"What is a muscle fibre?","A single muscle cell"
"What is contraction?","Muscle shortening"
"What is relaxation?","Muscle lengthening"
"What is isotonic contraction?","Muscle changes length"
"What is isometric contraction?","Muscle stays same length"
"What is concentric contraction?","Muscle shortens"
"What is eccentric contraction?","Muscle lengthens under tension"
"What is cardiac muscle?","Muscle of the heart"
"What is skeletal muscle?","Voluntary muscle"
"What is smooth muscle?","Involuntary muscle"
"What is the cardiovascular system?","Heart and blood vessels"
"What is heart rate?","Beats per minute"
"What is stroke volume?","Blood pumped per beat"
"What is cardiac output?","Heart rate multiplied by stroke volume"
"What is the respiratory system?","Breathing system"
"What is tidal volume?","Air per breath"
"What is vital capacity?","Maximum air exhaled"
"What is oxygen uptake?","Oxygen used by the body"
"What is haemoglobin?","Protein carrying oxygen"
"What is diffusion?","Movement from high to low concentration"
"What is aerobic respiration?","Energy production with oxygen"
"What is anaerobic respiration?","Energy production without oxygen"
"What is ATP?","Energy currency of the body"
"What is the ATP-PC system?","Immediate energy system"
"What is the glycolytic system?","Short-term energy system"
"What is the aerobic system?","Long-term energy system"
"What is lactic acid?","By-product of anaerobic exercise"
"What is oxygen debt?","Extra oxygen needed after exercise"
"What is EPOC?","Excess post exercise oxygen consumption"
"What is VO2 max?","Maximum oxygen uptake"
"What is recovery?","Return to resting state"
"What is muscle fatigue?","Reduced ability to contract"
"What are fast twitch fibres?","Explosive muscle fibres"
"What are slow twitch fibres?","Endurance muscle fibres"
"What is a motor unit?","Nerve and muscle fibres it controls"
"What is a neuromuscular junction?","Connection between nerve and muscle"
"What is the sliding filament theory?","Explains muscle contraction"
"What is actin?","Thin filament"
"What is myosin?","Thick filament"
"What is a sarcomere?","Functional unit of muscle"
"What is a tendon?","Connects muscle to bone"
"What is a ligament?","Connects bone to bone"
"What is cartilage?","Reduces friction in joints"
"What is synovial fluid?","Lubricates joints"
"What is the sagittal plane?","Divides body left and right"
"What is the frontal plane?","Divides body front and back"
"What is the transverse plane?","Divides body top and bottom"
"What is an axis?","Line of rotation"
"What is the transverse axis?","Runs left to right"
"What is the longitudinal axis?","Runs top to bottom"
"What is the frontal axis?","Runs front to back"
